DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Count Ugolino

who   : A Pisan count, betrayed and starved to death in a locked tower with his sons.
what  : A traitor frozen in the ice, gnawing forever the skull of the archbishop who doomed him.
where : Circle IX — Treachery (Antenora, to country and party).
why   : Betrayal answered with betrayal — and a hunger that outlasts death.
when  : Locked in the ice, telling the most terrible story in Hell.
how   : He lifts his mouth from Ruggieri's skull only to speak, then bends again to it.

class : Circle IX · Treachery · frozen in Cocytus
essence : count-ugolino.png
carbon apex : David Lee Wise (ROOT0)
— an artful intellect of Dante's Inferno (Dante Alighieri, inspiration only)
